and companies,
further away.

47:30.114 --> 47:35.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still, James Corner sees a huge
benefit in
creating spaces for people of
all walks of

47:35.119 --> 47:36.854 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
life to gather.

47:36.887 --> 47:40.157 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES CORNER: We're social
animals, and we
want to have a place to live,
and we want

47:40.191 --> 47:45.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to have a place to work, but we
also want
to have a place to participate
with other

47:45.229 --> 47:46.964 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
people.

47:46.997 --> 47:52.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I believe it is now, perhaps
more than
ever, more fundamental to what
it means to

47:52.169 --> 48:00.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be a democracy to be able to
foster greater
understanding, greater
tolerance, understand

48:00.411 --> 48:07.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
what it means to live in diverse
communities,
and to embrace that as something
enriching

48:07.284 --> 48:09.053 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and positive.

48:09.086 --> 48:12.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The High Line
itself continues
to expand, with construction of
a so-called

48:12.757 --> 48:17.795 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
