48:48.292 --> 48:51.228 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALEXI PAPPAS, Olympic Athlete:
My name is
Alexi Pappas.

48:51.262 --> 48:54.365 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And I'm a professional
long-distance runner
with Nike.

48:54.398 --> 48:58.769 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I'm also a filmmaker,
actress and poet.

48:58.803 --> 49:03.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This summer, I will race in my
first Olympic
Games in the 10,000 meters on
the track.

49:03.774 --> 49:06.377 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I will be running for Team
Greece.

49:06.410 --> 49:13.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm a duel citizen and decided
to compete
for Team Greece because I can
compete at the

49:13.651 --> 49:18.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
highest level, but I can also
reach a young
generation of girls who don't
necessarily

49:18.889 --> 49:24.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have the long-distance role
models that we
are lucky enough to have in the
United States.

49:24.094 --> 49:27.097 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, I'm very excited.

49:27.131 --> 49:32.436 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think I was a more serious
poet before I
was a serious runner.

49:32.469 --> 49:37.274 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What I find with writing that is
so special,
and in poetry in particular, is,
there's such

49:37.308 --> 49:38.809 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
an economy of words.

49:38.843 --> 49:45.082 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I like having absolute
freedom within
boundaries.

49:45.115 --> 49:47.852 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And in running, similarly, there
are these
limitations.

49:47.885 --> 49:51.922 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, in a race, you might have a
certain lane
that you have to stay in or a
certain number

49:51.956 --> 49:53.757 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of laps or a course.

49:53.791 --> 49:59.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But within those boundaries,
there's so much
room for freedom and creativity
and personality.

49:59.997 --> 50:02.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
"Breaking Tape."

50:02.800 --> 50:11.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"It happened like I imagine it
would feel
to throw open big double doors,
the kind from

50:11.275 --> 50:15.279 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a mansion or dollhouse.

50:15.312 --> 50:23.454 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I looked maybe like a very
strong princess
charging through the gate
towards the castle

50:23.487 --> 50:25.322 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I built myself."

50:25.356 --> 50:34.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"Tracktown" is a film that we
have just made
and premiered and is inspired by
my observations

50:34.198 --> 50:38.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and experiences as an elite
runner in Eugene,
Oregon.

50:38.736 --> 50:44.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when I moved to Eugene to
run a fifth
year with the Oregon Ducks after
I graduated

50:44.041 --> 50:49.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Dartmouth, I found that the town
and the community
embraced running in a way that I
had never

50:49.246 --> 50:50.514 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
seen before.

50:50.547 --> 50:55.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: "A goal is a dream with a
deadline"
-- Napoleon Hill.

50:55.119 --> 51:00.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALEXI PAPPAS: As a storyteller,
I want to
tell stories that I uniquely can
tell and

51:00.658 --> 51:05.362 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
stories in highly specific
worlds that most
people don't get the chance to
see.

51:05.396 --> 51:11.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so "Tracktown" is set in the
running world,
but is really about this girl,
and what is

51:11.101 --> 51:15.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
her life like on the track, but
especially
off the track.

51:15.039 --> 51:22.079 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Olympics have been on my
mind since my
dad brought my brother and me to
the 1996

51:22.112 --> 51:23.747 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Olympics in Atlanta.

51:23.781 --> 51:26.917 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I wanted to experience something
at the highest
level.

51:26.951 --> 51:32.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And being there, you're among,
like, greatness,
like great minds and great
bodies.

51:32.256 --> 51:37.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In terms of being nervous about
what people
are concerned about in Rio, it's
not the first

51:37.828 --> 51:39.630 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
thing on my mind.

51:39.663 --> 51:44.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think a lot of athletes
will agree that
we have worked for more than
four years for

51:44.034 --> 51:46.804 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
this dream, for our whole lives.

51:46.837 --> 51:52.209 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And nothing can stop most of us
from going
and realizing that dream.

51:52.242 --> 51:54.478 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
"Scary Things."

51:54.511 --> 52:01.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"The thing about scary things,
like spiders,
is that they do not scare me
nearly as much

52:02.019 --> 52:05.556 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as the things I want the most
things."

52:05.589 --> 52:10.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The things you're scared of, I
think, is a
reflection of how I feel every
day.

52:10.995 --> 52:16.934 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Like, as a runner and a
filmmaker, I wake
up every single day a little bit
nervous,

52:16.967 --> 52:19.103 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
but in a good way.

52:19.136 --> 52:24.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's always a goal that I
always have,
maybe a goal for that day or a
goal for longer-term,

52:24.675 --> 52:26.410 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
an Olympic dream.

52:26.443 --> 52:31.915 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's admitting that these
pursuits are really
hard, but they're really
beautiful.

52:31.949 --> 52:37.454 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I hope I always have
something that I
wake up being like a little bit
scared and

52:37.488 --> 52:39.223 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
